  <li id="comment-8949" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/15813090073506480020" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Delilah</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2008/02/consider-it/#comment-8949"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2008-02-05T21:10:00-05:00">Tuesday, February 5, 2008 at 9:10 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>As long as you are going through the effort of making your own granola, you could also make your own very small batch of apple sauce to go in. Just chop up a couple apples, put a bit of water in the pan and simmer away until the apples are soft enough to mush.</p>
    </div>

