    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://usingmainlyspoons.wordpress.com" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">louisem</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2008/02/consider-it/#comment-8958"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2008-02-06T15:12:00-05:00">Wednesday, February 6, 2008 at 3:12 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I love this recipe too &#8211; and can testify to its popularity as well. My parents, parents-in-law and sister-in-law are all converts!</>In the UK, I can get Brown Rice Syrup  from a wholefoods store (Bushwacker in Hammersmith) or from Whole Foods itself (in Kensington). I have also substituted Golden Syrup successfully, although it&#8217;s a bit sweet then (so you might want to lower the sugar), and not as crispy. For the apple sauce, I cook a big batch of Bramleys into unsweetened sauce and freeze it in little bags just for this recipe (175g).</p>
