    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Hi Molly. I&#8217;ve been on a homemade granola kick lately, but my other recipe uses butter, so I was happy to have your more healthy version. I&#8217;ve been eating &#8220;your&#8221; granola for the last few mornings, with rice milk or with yogurt. I LOVE the cinnamon, ginger, and brown sugar flavors mixing with the toasty, nutty flavors of the sesame seeds and sunflowers. I haven&#8217;t tried it yet, but I bet this recipe would be great mixed with dried apples or pears. &#8211;Your Ballard friend</p>
