  <li id="comment-8992" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/01292028011120349433" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Tina</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2008/02/consider-it/#comment-8992"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2008-03-15T18:13:00-04:00">Saturday, March 15, 2008 at 6:13 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I finally made this recipe last weekend, and it&#8217;s fabulous!  Thanks so much for posting it!  I didn&#8217;t follow the recipe to the letter; I used a mixture of sesame and flax seeds, and substituted pumpkin seeds, which I already had, for sunflower seeds (which I didn&#8217;t).  I&#8217;ve been eating it for lunch all week w/ strained yogurt.  I will definitely be making this over and over.  Thank you!</p>
