      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/01493708300940204826" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Molly</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2008/02/consider-it/#comment-9003"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2008-08-17T16:27:00-04:00">Sunday, August 17, 2008 at 4:27 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Lynne, you can definitely keep it at room temperature.  I have tended to keep mine in the fridge as an insurance policy of sorts, since it has so many nuts and I worry about them going rancid, but you know, you don&#8217;t really <>need<> to.  So yes, use those pretty jars!</p>
